               uth of his ſon Ieſus Chriſt,
ſaying:Math. 3 17. 
               This is my welbeloued ſonne,
               Deut. 18. 
               in whome I am
well pleaſed, heare him. And whoſoeuer will not harken
vnto the wordes, which hee ſhall ſpeake in my
name, I will require it of him: I will be reuenged of
him (ſaith God) Of this, witneſſeth Peter alſo, laying
The time will come Paul
