one The broad way, and the other The narrow vvay,
ſaying,
               Mat. 7. 13, 14. Enter in at the ſtrait gate: for wide is the gate,
and broad is the way that leadeth to deſtruction, and
many there be which goe in thereat. But ſtrait is the
gate, and narrovv is the vvay vvhich leadeth into life,
and fevv there be that finde it. Note diligently theſe
wordes of the trueth. He ſheweth heere two gates, two
